data.title: Eh ... wouldn't go back.
data.text: Hostess and waiter not very friendly or welcoming, a bit run down, kind of dirty - could use some basic repairs around the place. Food was only just OK. Fajita meat had big chunks of fat in it, shrimp was over cook and hard, chicken was dried out, not many veggies. Our waiter took our plate before we were through with our fajitas for two and was completely inattentive to our table. I asked twice for a glass of water with my margarita. Never did get it. Too small an area for a large mariachi band. They were good ... Just REALLY loud. Love El Loro Eagan and Big Lake! This one ... not so much. Good thing we were with good company.

data.title: Food was great!! Waiter was rude.
data.text: I heard such good things about El Loro & was excited to try it with a few friends. The restaurant is clean & well maintained. We went on a Saturday night around 8pm & it wasn't busy at all. We had an male waiter & from the start, he was very rude. He rushed us while we were ordering & he talked over us when we were trying to ask him questions about the menu. He then got one of our orders wrong & another waiter came and got us the correct plate of food right away, but then our initial waiter came back & had an attitude about the mistake he made. He also didn't check back at our table & ask if we needed anything or refill our drinks. Other than the rude customer service, the food was delicious. I recommend the chicken or beef tacos, chimichanga, & any of the of burritos with queso! The margaritas are great too & cheap during happy hour (medium margarita for only $6.50). Happy hour is from 8pm-close. I recommend this place but due to the customer service, I will be going to another location.

data.title: Fast and friendly
data.text: This is a great place to eat it's wonderful.  It's a quaint little place it's cute inside. And the food is great.

data.title: Great food
data.text: Fast friendly service. They have a large selection and the prices won't break the bank. I've never walked out of there hungry. Actually full I can't eat it all and the food tastes great.

data.title: Fast, friendly, fair.
data.text: On a search for a good restaurant close to home, this one takes the cake! We have been in here enough times now that we are greeted with a friendly smile of recognition. The margaritas are strong, the nachos are cheap and plenty filling. No matter how busy the parking lot looks we are always seated promptly and receive great service.

data.title: Good and Friendly
data.text:
Stopped in for lunch. Good parking, security not a problem and not a run down establishment.
Several lunch entries to choose from and fetured specials for both lunch and dinner. a happy hour is later in the PM. Started out with a free chips and salsa, delivered by a friendly waitress,
Ordered off the lunch menu area ( reasonable priced) . Food was delivered promptly and tasted very good. Overall a very good experience and will return again.

data.title: Less than average service and food
data.text: The service was not acceptable. Other reviews mention the food comes out fast, that is true. Our waitress only came once to our table just to take the order. She never once again stopped to ask how is everything or to ask if we needed refills. She did stop to drop the bill and run. The food was not up to Mexican food standards. If you like Minnesotan food disguised as mexican food this is the place for you. The margaritas weren't good either. To top it off the place was swarming with flies. The only reason I am giving them a 2 star is because my husband did liked their food as he loves Minnesotan food disguised as mexican food otherwise it would be a 0-1 star.

data.title: Taste of  Mexico...
data.text: My family frequently visits El Loro. They've been one of our go-to's if we're in the mood for something quick and delicious. It seems like a family run place, but I can't confirm that. All I know is that most of the staff has been there a decade or more and they rarely make a mistake. The drink  glasses are almost never empty and I should mention they make a great margarita. They make great food too. The lunch specials are reasonably priced and would be a great choice if you're in the mood for a sit down lunch but you don't have a ton of time. I'm usually very surprised with how fast the food comes out.

data.title: OK
data.text: My family and I dine in on Mothers Day and it was not the greatest experience. The food was not good, and the waitress what just plain rude. No customer service at all. Will not return.

data.title: New even worth a one star
data.text: Don't know where to start. Rude hostess . Rude waiter . Small portions. Over priced. Loud and anxious customers. Watched bus boys . Do half way clean up on tables.

data.title: Fajitas for Two-Wonderful!
data.text: We dine here often and a have always had very good food and service.  The fajitas for two are my favorite, shrimp,chicken,beef,and tender pork. It's a big portion, we always take some home.  Chips and salsa are very good too.  The same staff have been serving us for years, they know their stuff.

data.title: AWESOME EVERY TIME
data.text: We eat at El Loro in Coon Rapids all the time. The service is fast, friendly, and the food is always hot and super tasty.  The BEST margaritas in the states.....hands down.  Careful, they sneak up on you.

data.title: Our local favorite for Mexican foods!
data.text: El Loro is our local favorite for good food, service and value.  We enjoy the lunch menu for value since this is when we typically go out to eat.  Always quick and good.

data.title: Mediocre Mexican food
data.text: We were excited to try the El Lor I that opened in Lexington Minnesota. The large number of people there was a good sign. The place is big and can handle a big group. The waiter was attentive. The food was bland. It is Mexican food made for American taste buds. They did serve warm chips which is a nice touch.    Try it if your in the area but don't make a special trip.

data.title: No Thanks
data.text:
I've eaten at this restaurant several times and thought the food and service was pretty good. However, the last time I went there will be my last. Last summer we went there and were seated in a booth along the windows. There were dead flies all over the window ledge and so many flying around biting my ankles under the table it was horrible.
If you go past the place any time take a look, the back door to the kitchen (not far from the dumpster) will be propped wide open. So it's no mystery where the flies are getting in. I hate giving a review about something like this but it is what I experienced.

data.title: Great Mexican Food
data.text: When ever I order from E Loro or go in to eat I'm not disappointed. The food is always good and the service excellent.

data.title: Second chance strikes out again
data.text: Wife and I tried out El Loro again.  Still dirty. Still poor food. We each ordered tacos. She wouldn't finish hers. I had most of mine. Very mediocre beef. I don't get this place.  There are many other fine Mexican places in the area. We had bottled beer this time which was ok.

data.title: Good food and atmosphere
data.text: Bobber51 sounds like a whiny 4 yr old who didnt get a toy when he went shopping with mommy(bitter party of 1)....Anyway been coming here for 10 yrs always great service and everything I have ordered has been good...Sure after coming here probably 100 times over the 10 yrs they have a bad day but I maybe recall 1-2 times and it was extremely busy those times.

data.title: No hot water in the men's bathroom, need I say more?
data.text: It makes you suspicious when a place seats you next to a pile of dirty dishes on a cart. It certainly doesn't make the meal appealing and it certainly does stink. Yuck. That should have been my first sign. Plus the room could have been cleaner. It made it worse when they handed us dirty menus.  We should have left then; my fault. I got up to wash my hands in the men's room. No hot water. I had to wash my hands with cold water. Is this even legal? Which brings up the bigger question - where do the employees wash their hands? My daughter couldn't even use their napkins. They smelled too moldy.  As for the food, the first bowl of salsa was OK. The second, not so good. It had an off taste to it, something like mold. The waiter was unfriendly and short with us. Would have been nice if he smiled.  My wife asked him questions and he wasn't helpful. Wife and daughter ordered chicken and it was so bad they didn't eat it. It tasted microwaved to them. It sat too long. Probably explains why they can't substitute. When they delivered my plate, the waiter had a hot pad on his hand. His thumb was stuck in the middle of my lettuce. Gross. I ate only my pork. All I can say is it was better than the chicken. They were re roofing the place, but that can't explain the uncleanliness. Plus there is NO excuse for no hot water in a men's room. As my daughter said, it truly replicated eating in Mexico...

data.title: Good food, good location
data.text: I met a friend at El Loro yesterday afternoon for an early dinner. As I live 30 minutes away, I hadnt' been to El Loro before. It was a beautiful day and we sat on the patio. The patio was comfortable and private, though the wait staff didn't make it outside as frequently as we would have liked. We each ordered a blended alcoholic drink and they were fabulous. We also each had Quesadillas Rellenas with chicken. The food was fantastic and my friend loved their spicy ranch-like dipping sauce for the endless chips. It was located about 5 minutes from the movie theater which might make this place a regular location for Girls Night Out.
